<br>
This dagger isn't bad, but honestly, to people able to pass Rallos Zek, this is a very sad effect. If you are not in a guild that is in tier 4, please think about the fact that guild that are indeed reaching tier4 have spent months in VP/ntov/ST/ssra/VT to reach that stage, during these months they have gattered a fair share of loot. Then they got to PoP and went through bertox, saryrn, Mithaniel marr, Agnaar, Terris thule, etc, again collecting more loots in the process, then went on to kill Rallos, once again getting more loot.<br>
<br>
This is a fact, to people able to get there, this dagger is sub-par. Like it has been mentioned, focus items at this level are rarely summoned by the bag, I myself have never cast the bag spell, I simply don't need it, I only summon focus items one or 2 at a time and only wear earing myself. Most caster have at least level 4 casting focuses by the time they get to tier 4, some of them having better than lvl 4 focus (VT/PoP gear).<br>
<br>
What people are saying is not that this dagger sucks and Joe Sebilis wouldn't use it, but that the ubers who are in the elemental planes see this as sub-par, wich is true.<br>
<br>
So if you wanna say that this dagger rocks, please mention the fact that you are not flagged for that zone and consider that on the way to getting flagged for elemental planes, you'll get better gear than this most likely. Then maybe you'll understand why high end mages are not getting a hard on from it. <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=75721">Woon</a><!--EZCODE LINK END-->  <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://tde.e-slackers.net/">&lt;TDE&gt;</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> <br>
