Chances are good that uber players getting this item will have little need for the summoned focus items.  Chances aren't as good that the not-as-uber players that see this item in the next year <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>will</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->.  But either way, it eliminates the need to memorize a pain-in-the ass spell and it has a zero cast time.  Since it's on an item with good stats, you don't have to go searching in your bags when someone wants a focus item.  Someone asks for a focus item, 1 click, trade, all set.  <br>
<br>
If every item had a &quot;wow&quot; effect on it then pretty soon we'd either be overpowered or they'd run out of suitable effects to put on items.  Items with really powerful affects are usually <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>rare</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->, not just hard to get.  <br>
<br>
<br>
There have been soo many times in the past that ubers way overestimated how much they should be rewarded for killing mob X in zone Y, and sometimes it's fun to laugh when they bitch about minor things like this.. especially when they're the same ones that cop a self-righteous attitude about things like spoilers.<br>
<br>
Also note that I said that the item should have no effect at all.  If it had <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>no</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> effect, people probably wouldn't be bitching so much.  People aren't satisfied with seeing something as a bonus, they see &quot;effect:&quot; and if it's not something offense or devensively powerful it's automatically &quot;flawed rvr&quot; or something.  <br>
